
[1]monotony

   MONOT'ONY, n. [Gr. sole, and sound.]

   1. Uniformity of tone or sound; want of inflections of voice in
   speaking; want of cadence or modulation.

   2. Uniformity; sameness.

   At sea, every thing that breaks the monotony of the surrounding expanse
   attracts attention.
